About the assignment

Happy Customer Bank is a mid-sized private bank that deals in all kinds of banking products, like Savings accounts, Current accounts, investment products, credit products, among other offerings.

The bank also cross-sells products to its existing customers and to do so they use different kinds of communication like tele-calling, e-mails, recommendations on net banking, mobile banking, etc.

In this case, the Happy Customer Bank wants to cross sell its credit cards to its existing customers. The bank has identified a set of customers that are eligible for taking these credit cards.

Now, the bank is looking for your help in identifying customers that could show higher intent towards a recommended credit card, given:


Customer details (gender, age, region etc.)
Details of his/her relationship with the bank (ChannelCode,Vintage, 'AvgAsset_Value etc.)

Data Dictionary is given below:

Train Data
Variable

Definition

ID : Unique Identifier for a row

Gender : Gender of the Customer

Age : Age of the Customer (in Years)

Region_Code : Code of the Region for the customers

Occupation : Occupation Type for the customer

Channel_Code : Acquisition Channel Code for the Customer (Encoded)

Vintage : Vintage for the Customer (In Months)

Credit_Product : If the Customer has any active credit product (Home loan,

Personal loan, Credit Card etc.)

AvgAccountBalance : Average Account Balance for the Customer in last 12 Months

Is_Active : If the Customer is Active in last 3 Months

Is_Lead(Target) : If the Customer is interested for the Credit Card

0 : Customer is not interested

1 : Customer is interested

Test Data

All variables except Is_Lead


Create a predictive model from the given data to help the bank take a call on which customers have a propensity to opt for a credit card so that they can market it to them. 

Share your final recommendation as a power point presentation. Think of yourself as an MBA who is in a decision science role. 